We’ve already done the first background step (loaded Hamilcar, set `$DynamicalMetric=False`, `$ManualSmearing=True`). Next we should systematically set up this specific theory.

Given your Hamiltonian matches the Maxwell-theory template, we should follow the same pattern:

**Step 1 (single step): define constants, fields, momenta, multipliers, and smearings**

Concretely, I propose to run:

```wolfram
(* Constant *)
DefConstantSymbol[Coupling750dbd1c, PrintAs->"\[Alpha]"];

(* Canonical fields *)
DefCanonicalField[Field2a3728e5[], FieldSymbol->"\[ScriptCapitalA]0p", MomentumSymbol->"\[CapitalPi]\[ScriptCapitalA]0p"];
DefCanonicalField[Field37d48fd1[-a], FieldSymbol->"\[ScriptCapitalA]1m", MomentumSymbol->"\[CapitalPi]\[ScriptCapitalA]1m"];

(* Multipliers *)
DefTensor[Field2a3728e5LagrangeMultiplier[], M3, PrintAs->"\[Lambda]\[ScriptCapitalA]0p"];
DefTensor[Field37d48fd1LagrangeMultiplier[-a], M3, PrintAs->"\[Lambda]\[ScriptCapitalA]1m"];

(* Smearing functions *)
DefTensor[SmearingFField2a3728e5[], M3, PrintAs->"\[ScriptF]"];
DefTensor[SmearingFField37d48fd1[-a], M3, PrintAs->"\[ScriptF]"];
DefTensor[SmearingSField2a3728e5[], M3, PrintAs->"\[ScriptS]"];
DefTensor[SmearingSField37d48fd1[-a], M3, PrintAs->"\[ScriptS]"];

(* Total Hamiltonian density *)
TotalHamiltonianDensity =
  ConjugateMomentumField2a3728e5[]*Field2a3728e5LagrangeMultiplier[] +
  (ConjugateMomentumField37d48fd1[-a]*ConjugateMomentumField37d48fd1[a])/(2*Coupling750dbd1c) +
  ConjugateMomentumField37d48fd1[a]*CD[-a][Field2a3728e5[]] -
  (Coupling750dbd1c*CD[-a][Field37d48fd1[-b]]*CD[b][Field37d48fd1[a]])/2 +
  (Coupling750dbd1c*CD[-b][Field37d48fd1[-a]]*CD[b][Field37d48fd1[a]])/2;

TotalHamiltonianDensity = Recanonicalize[TotalHamiltonianDensity];
```

This will fully define the Hamiltonian system inside Hamilcar so we can then:

- Take `VarD` w.r.t. multipliers to find primary constraints.
- Then check their time preservation via Poisson brackets.

Should I run this whole “Step 1” block now (one call that uses each of the Hamilcar/xAct functions only once)?
